{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/09-01-feeling-badly-about-saying-no","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"platforms":[{"name":"Brunow","introducedAt":"2017.01.20"}],"title":"Feeling Badly About Saying No","color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"date: 2016-09-01T00:05:16-05:00"}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/09-01-feeling-badly-about-saying-no"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I’ve been on a kick lately about saying no to things. Apparently I’ve been pushed to my limit and can’t handle anything else so everything is turning into a no. But I still feel like a jerk for saying no and I don’t like feeling like a jerk. I start to apologize for saying no when I really meant it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2016":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016","abstract":[],"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2016","title":"2016","type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}],"title":"Brunow","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/brunow","role":"collection"},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/Archive":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/